---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact — Nate Cowperthwaite"
  description="Chef, self-taught developer, and co-founder building tools rooted in real kitchen problems. Say hi."
  side="dev"
>
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
    <section class="about-hero hero-gradient-bg">
      <div class="orb-container" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="orb orb-blue"></div>
        <div class="orb orb-indigo"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-hero-inner">
        <div class="animate-fade-in-up">
          <span class="badge badge-blue">&#128100; About Me</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="about-hero-title animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay:0.07s">
          Chef by trade.<br />
          <span class="shimmer-text">Builder by necessity.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="about-hero-sub animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay:0.14s">
          I've spent 10+ years in professional kitchens — working the line, leading BOH teams,
          and running food service from scratch every single day. In 2025 I started building
          software to fix the problems no existing tool bothered to solve.
          That side project grew into something real. I'm not a developer looking for work —
          I'm a chef who codes because the problems are worth solving.
        </p>
        <p class="about-hero-back animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay:0.20s">
          <a href="/dev" class="inline-link">&larr; Back to Dev Home</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== WHO I AM ===== -->
    <section class="section section-blue-tint">
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Who I Am</h2>
      <p class="section-sub reveal">The honest version.</p>

      <div class="who-grid stagger">

        <div class="who-card card card-blue-left reveal">
          <div class="who-card-icon">&#128298;</div>
          <h3 class="who-card-title">Still a Working Chef</h3>
          <p class="who-card-text">
            Kitchen work is still my day job. I've written menus, managed food cost,
            led BOH teams through the chaos of service, and done every unglamorous shift
            that keeps an operation running. Cooking isn't a backstory — it's the whole point.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="who-card card card-blue-left reveal">
          <div class="who-card-icon">&#128736;&#65039;</div>
          <h3 class="who-card-title">Self-Taught Developer</h3>
          <p class="who-card-text">
            No bootcamp. No CS degree. I learned by building things I genuinely needed —
            recipe tooling, kitchen ops automation, AI-assisted workflows.
            Every gap in my knowledge got filled by a real problem that demanded a solution.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="who-card card card-blue-left reveal">
          <div class="who-card-icon">&#129514;</div>
          <h3 class="who-card-title">Problem-First Mindset</h3>
          <p class="who-card-text">
            Nothing I build starts from "what's a cool tech stack." It starts from a specific,
            repeating friction point — something slow, something missing, something that
            should already exist but doesn't. Irritation is a better motivator than inspiration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="who-card card card-blue-left reveal">
          <div class="who-card-icon">&#129302;</div>
          <h3 class="who-card-title">Deep in AI &amp; Agentic Tooling</h3>
          <p class="who-card-text">
            MCP, AI APIs, agentic workflows — I use this stack daily, not to chase a trend
            but because it's genuinely the fastest path from a real problem to a working solution.
            Especially when you're building solo and time is your scarcest resource.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-animated"></div>

    <!-- ===== WHAT I BUILD ===== -->
    <section class="section section-blue-wash">
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">What I Build</h2>
      <p class="section-sub reveal">Focused tools. Real workflows. No roadmap theater.</p>

      <div class="build-list stagger">

        <div class="build-item reveal">
          <span class="build-dot">&#9658;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Kitchen &amp; food ops tools</strong> — recipe scaling, food cost tracking,
            prep management, dietary planning. The software commercial kitchens actually need
            at a price point that doesn't require a corporate budget.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="build-item reveal">
          <span class="build-dot">&#9658;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Workflow automation</strong> — if I'm doing the same task manually more than twice,
            I'm building something to handle it. Time saved in the kitchen compounds fast.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="build-item reveal">
          <span class="build-dot">&#9658;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>AI integrations with actual utility</strong> — not chatbots stapled onto
            existing products, but agents designed around a specific task that make that task
            meaningfully faster or more accurate.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="build-item reveal">
          <span class="build-dot">&#9658;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Whatever I'm annoyed by this week</strong> — the best projects start with
            "why doesn't this exist yet" and end with something I actually use every day.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-animated"></div>

    <!-- ===== CONTACT ===== -->
    <section class="section section-blue-tint">
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Say Hi</h2>
      <p class="section-sub reveal">
        Not hiring, not for hire. But if something here caught your attention — I'm around.
      </p>

      <div class="contact-grid stagger">

        <!-- Email -->
        <a
          href="mailto:shadowwalkernc@gmail.com"
          class="contact-card card card-glow-blue reveal"
          aria-label="Send an email to Nate"
        >
          <div class="contact-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9993;&#65039;</div>
          <div class="contact-card-body">
            <div class="contact-card-label">Email</div>
            <div class="contact-card-value">shadowwalkernc@gmail.com</div>
            <p class="contact-card-note">
              Best for anything worth an actual conversation — feedback, ideas, a weird
              collaboration, or just wanting to talk shop about kitchen tech. I respond within a couple of days.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-card-cta">Send a message &rarr;</div>
        </a>

        <!-- GitHub -->
        <a
          href="https://github.com/ShadowWalkerNC"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="contact-card card card-glow-blue reveal"
          aria-label="View Nate's GitHub profile"
        >
          <div class="contact-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#128049;</div>
          <div class="contact-card-body">
            <div class="contact-card-label">GitHub</div>
            <div class="contact-card-value">ShadowWalkerNC</div>
            <p class="contact-card-note">
              Everything I'm actively building lives here. Open an issue, leave feedback,
              or dig through the repos. Pull requests on anything public are genuinely welcome.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-card-cta">View profile &rarr;</div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ---- Section tints ---- */
.section-blue-tint {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg,
    rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.04) 0%,
    transparent 100%);
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.12);
}
.section-blue-wash {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg,
    rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.06) 0%,
    rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.03) 100%);
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.10);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.10);
}

/* ---- Hero ---- */
.about-hero {
  position: relative;
  padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.18);
}
.about-hero::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg,
    rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.07) 0%,
    transparent 60%);
  pointer-events: none;
}
.about-hero-inner {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 2;
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  text-align: center;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0;
}
.about-hero-inner .badge { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
.about-hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
  font-weight: 900;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  line-height: 1.1;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.about-hero-sub {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 560px;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.about-hero-back { font-size: 0.88rem; }

/* ---- Who I Am grid ---- */
.who-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem;
}
.who-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.6rem;
  padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
}
.card-blue-left {
  border-left: 3px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.30);
  background: linear-gradient(135deg,
    rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05) 0%,
    var(--bg-elevated) 60%);
}
.card-blue-left:hover { border-left-color: var(--accent-blue); }
.who-card-icon { font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1; }
.who-card-title {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  margin: 0;
}
.who-card-text {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin: 0;
}

/* ---- What I Build list ---- */
.build-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1rem;
  max-width: 680px;
}
.build-item {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.7;
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.04);
  border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.10);
  transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
}
.build-item:hover {
  border-color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.25);
  background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.07);
}
.build-item strong { color: var(--text-primary); }
.build-dot {
  color: var(--accent-blue);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  margin-top: 0.28rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* ---- Contact cards ---- */
.contact-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem;
  max-width: 720px;
}
.contact-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  padding: 2rem 1.75rem 1.5rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  border-left: 3px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.25);
  background: linear-gradient(135deg,
    rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.04) 0%,
    var(--bg-elevated) 50%);
  transition: transform 0.22s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1),
              box-shadow 0.22s ease,
              border-color 0.22s ease;
}
.contact-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  border-left-color: var(--accent-blue);
}
.contact-card-icon {
  font-size: 2.4rem;
  line-height: 1;
  filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 8px rgba(37,99,235,0.20));
}
.contact-card-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; flex: 1; }
.contact-card-label {
  font-size: 0.68rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.6);
}
.contact-card-value {
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent-blue);
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}
.contact-card-note {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}
.contact-card-cta {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent-blue);
  letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-6px);
  transition: opacity 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
}
.contact-card:hover .contact-card-cta {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

/* ---- Responsive ---- */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .about-hero   { padding: 3.5rem 1rem 2.5rem; }
  .who-grid     { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .contact-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
